=======

Schuhpalast Pinkus (Pinkus' Shoe Palace) has earned a place in history
as one of the earliest surviving Lubitsch films.

Sally Pinkus is a German-Jewish boy who takes a job as a shoe store clerk
after being expelled from school for goofing around. Soon fired for trying
to court the owner's daughter, Pinkus lands another job in a more 'upmarket'
shoe salon, only to be fired again, before charming a rich benefactress to
fund his ultimate dream.

